ALES Records, 1920-1962

Kheel Center for Labor-Management Documentation & Archives
Cornell University Library

DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY

Title:
ALES Records, 1920-1962
Repository:
Kheel Center for Labor-Management Documentation & Archives
Collection Number:
5225
Abstract:
Pamphlets and other documents re Brookwood Labor College available in this substantial collection. Unpublished guide Available.
Creator:
American Labor Education Service (ALES)
Quanitities:
125.5 cubic feet
Language:
Collection material in English
Access to the collections in the Kheel Center is restricted. Please contact a reference archivist for access to these materials.
Conditions Governing Use

This collection must be used in keeping with the Kheel Center Information Sheet and Procedures for Document Use.
INFORMATION FOR USERS
Preferred Citation

ALES Records #5225. Kheel Center for Labor-Management Documentation and Archives, Cornell University Library.
Related Materials

Related Collections: 5225 C: ALES Course Materials 5225 E: ALES Labor Education Records 5225 I: ALES International Labor Records 5225 L: ALES Labor Plays 5225 S: ALES Scrapbooks 5657: American Labor Education Service Additional Documents

Scope and Contents
including local unions, state and regional bosies, international unions, departments of the AFL-CIO and organizations related to labor and workers' education. Filed with correspondence are conference programs and speeches and pamphlets. ALES was the only U.S. member of the International Federation of Workers Education Association. The following are represented: AFL-CIO, Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, International Union of Electrical Workers, International Federation of Workers' Education Association, International Confederation of Free Trade Unions, ILGWU, International Labour Office, Industrial and Labor Relations Review, Jewish Labor Committee, Kentucky State Federation of labor, Labor and Nation, Labor Education Association of Philadelphia, International Association of Machinists, Massachusetts CIO Council, Meat Cutters and Butcher Workmen, Michigan CIO Council, Minnesota CIO Council, Montana State Federation of Labor, National Farmers Union, National Institute of Labor Education, New York City Central Labor Council, Ohio CIO Council, Oil Chemical and Atomic Weapons Workers International Union, National Alliance of Postal Workers, Religion and Labor Foundation, American State County and Municipal Employees, American Federation of Teachers, Local 189, Textile Workers Union of America, United Automobile Workers, Workers Defense League

including local unions, state and regional bosies, international unions, departments of the AFL-CIO and organizations related to labor and workers' education. Filed with correspondence are conference programs and speeches and pamphlets. ALES was the only U.S. member of the International Federation of Workers Education Association. The following are represented: AFL-CIO, Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America, International Union of Electrical Workers, International Federation of Workers' Education Association, International Confederation of Free Trade Unions, ILGWU, International Labour Office, Industrial and Labor Relations Review, Jewish Labor Committee, Kentucky State Federation of labor, Labor and Nation, Labor Education Association of Philadelphia, International Association of Machinists, Massachusetts CIO Council, Meat Cutters and Butcher Workmen, Michigan CIO Council, Minnesota CIO Council, Montana State Federation of Labor, National Farmers Union, National Institute of Labor Education, New York City Central Labor Council, Ohio CIO Council, Oil Chemical and Atomic Weapons Workers International Union, National Alliance of Postal Workers, Religion and Labor Foundation, American State County and Municipal Employees, American Federation of Teachers, Local 189, Textile Workers Union of America, United Automobile Workers, Workers Defense League
